      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-b border-tjb-lavender-300/40 pb-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-tjb-charcoal text-lg mb-2">How much does a postpartum doula cost per hour?</h3>
          <p class="text-tjb-gray leading-relaxed">Postpartum doulas typically charge $25-$50 per hour for daytime support in most areas. In major metros, rates can reach $60-$75 per hour. Overnight support is priced per shift, usually $200-$400 per night. Package deals for multiple days of support often bring the effective hourly rate down.</p>
        </div>
